cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.CC 

The paper proposes a machine learning-based method for searching for proofs of polynomial inequalities within the framework of semi-algebraic proof systems. This involves learning an embedding of the polynomials and guiding the choice of inference rules using deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with developing a learning-based algorithm for a computational task. The paper also involves mathematical optimization and symbolic computation, which are covered by sub-categories cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
